1
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:18,120
Shao.

2
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:22,160
Mr. Wang, about that contract, I...

3
00:00:25,880 --> 00:00:27,120
Mr. Wang, well...

4
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:31,960
Why isn't your contract ready yet?

5
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:33,360
Can you do this job or not?

6
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:34,840
I quit.

7
00:00:34,920 --> 00:00:36,580
Ren Zhen, don't be so willful.

8
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:53,040
Excuse me.

9
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:55,520
How long does it take to get to Wenquan County?

10
00:00:55,520 --> 00:00:56,800
About an hour.

11
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:58,880
Thank you.

12
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:00,210
You're welcome.

13
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:21,050
Where are you going?

14
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:21,880
Well,

15
00:01:22,039 --> 00:01:23,960
Grandpa Bate's sheep is ruminating badly.

16
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:25,600
I'm taking it to the county to see a vet.

17
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:27,560
Remember to bring back my rubber shoes.

18
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:28,820
Alright. Don't worry.

19
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:29,760
I'm leaving now.

20
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:31,090
Uncle Tuoka, Aunt Guli.

21
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,440
Bye. Take care.

22
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:34,780
Call me Secretary.

23
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,640
Even if they fly to the sky, they're still kids I watched grow up.

24
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:38,720
Go, go, go.

25
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,560
Is it okay now?

26
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,000
I fed it some medicine.

27
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,330
It ate some grass when passing the bazaar.

28
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:50,039
It should be fine now.

29
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,000
That's good.

30
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:55,039
These sheep are Bate's life.

31
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,530
I'll make some skewers.

32
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:59,210
We can chat while we eat.

33
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:01,100
The last time we met

34
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:04,540
was when you were taking the village official exam.

35
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,160
Mr. Yin.

36
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:12,080
Do you think my returning to Xia Village

37
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:14,200
was a wrong choice?

38
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,660
Block the view.

39
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,890
We can't do it in front of it.

40
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:30,560
Graduated from Peking University.

41
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,680
The chosen one.

42
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:34,210
Regret coming back?

43
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,920
I... I didn't mean that.

44
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,560
I just feel

45
00:02:38,079 --> 00:02:39,410
it's been three months,

46
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:42,120
and Xia Village is still the same Xia Village.

47
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,040
I've been here for 13 years.

48
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:46,560
Let me ask you.

49
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,880
Between a place's education and economic development,

50
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,440
which one is faster and which is slower?

51
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:53,160
They definitely complement each other.

52
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:54,400
Exactly.

53
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,079
You just took office.

54
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,400
What's the rush?

55
00:02:58,920 --> 00:02:59,850
Keep skewering.

56
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,880
I'll go cut some more onions.

57
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:12,280
Hello. You must be in the wrong place.

58
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,120
Xiaojun.

59
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,400
You've grown so tall

60
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:17,520
and handsome.

61
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:19,400
You've kept in good shape too.

62
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,560
Wait, who are you?

63
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,480
This place looks exactly

64
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:23,560
like the photos.

65
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,160
As for you,

66
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:27,280
you've really impressed me.

67
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:28,200
Wait.

68
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,680
Keep your hands to yourself.

69
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,520
Ren Zhen.

70
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:33,800
Mr. Yin.

71
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,480
Guliqi.

72
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:48,200
Stop bringing me meat. I can't finish it.

73
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,720
My dad just slaughtered a new sheep

74
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:51,960
and asked me to bring some for you to try.

75
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:54,240
Thank your dad for me when you go back.

76
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,160
Got it.

77
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,360
It's fine.

78
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:15,140
This life will pass very quickly.

79
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,320
Mr. Yin,

80
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,880
how come I've never heard

81
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,160
you have a daughter?

82
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,320
Ren Zhen is

83
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:25,890
like a real daughter to me despite having no blood relation.

84
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,440
She was in the last class I taught

85
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,100
before I went to aid Xinjiang.

86
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:32,159
We have kept in touch ever since.

87
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:33,620
She likes to call me...

88
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,520
Dad Yin.

89
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,360
Where is Xiaojun?

90
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,560
Xiaojun?

91
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,770
He went to Shanghai for an internship.

92
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:42,730
His mother also went there to take care of him.

93
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:45,800
Still thinking about Xiacun Village?

94
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,400
I want to develop e-commerce

95
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:49,370
to sell all the crops in the village

96
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,330
so everyone can earn a bit more.

97
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:53,840
The leaders allocated some funds

98
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:56,700
to set up a professional livestreaming room for us.

99
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,400
But the hard part right now is

100
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:01,880
that we have no e-commerce talents available.

101
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,210
If there are no talents, just go find them.

102
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,200
Talents

103
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:07,450
won't just come knocking on your door.

104
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:15,080
Try some Xinjiang Pi La Hong.

105
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,700
You must all be hungry.

106
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:20,920
They are all my students.

107
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,010
Let me formally introduce you.

108
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:24,680
Jiao Li,

109
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:27,080
Party Secretary of Xia Village.

110
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:27,880
Hello.

111
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:31,440
Did I just assault a state official?

112
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:35,200
Ren Zhen.

113
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,200
I remember you've always been

114
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,200
working in e-commerce in Hangzhou.

115
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:39,800
Yes.

116
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,380
I worked at Shangle Group.

117
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:42,640
That's a top-tier

118
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:44,770
live-streaming e-commerce company.

119
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,680
It's alright.

120
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,440
Zhenzhen.

121
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,640
You were working day and night.

122
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,740
How do you have time to travel?

123
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,880
I quit.

124
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,440
Have some more barbecue.

125
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:03,840
I remember you used to be chubby.

126
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,560
Now you're so thin.

127
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:09,520
You've been meaning to visit me for years.

128
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,160
You didn't quit

129
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:13,280
just to visit me this time, did you?

130
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:15,240
I couldn't bear that.

131
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:17,920
It was just on the way.

132
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,000
But the difficulty right now

133
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:26,400
is that we have no e-commerce talent.

134
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:28,040
Zhenzhen.

135
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:31,180
Have you thought about finding a job?

136
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,800
Uncle Yin, I just quit.

137
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,400
I want to rest for a while.

138
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:38,120
Why rest at such a young age?

139
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,220
How about this.

140
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:41,420
You should go to Jiao Li's.

141
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,480
Sure.

142
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:45,880
Our village is just developing its e-commerce business.

143
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,640
We really need a talent like you.

144
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:50,080
Jiao Li is new to grassroots work.

145
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,210
Although his village is small,

146
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:54,620
it has great potential for development.

147
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,000
Look, we young people

148
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:58,480
don't necessarily have to make a living in big cities

149
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,440
to seek development.

150
00:06:59,440 --> 00:07:00,600
The countryside is where you go from zero to one,

151
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,680
the most authentic place to strive.

152
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,320
Right, Mr. Yin?

153
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:02,880
Right.

154
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,520
What a dramatic thing to say.

155
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:09,450
I don't want to strive. I just want to lie flat.

156
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,520
Actually, Uncle Yin,

157
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,800
I just came to see you.

158
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,520
I'm flying to Urumqi tomorrow.

159
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,480
I want to head south to relax.

160
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,720
Well, if you've planned it,

161
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,320
I won't keep you.

162
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,720
Later,

163
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,170
Jiao Li, you see her off.

164
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,000
Okay.

165
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:29,080
Then I'll take you to the station later.

166
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,160
Okay.

167
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:36,480
Thank you.

168
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:37,140
No problem.

169
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,159
Can I ask you

170
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:43,720
about live stream operations later?

171
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,720
Of course you can.

172
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,840
I don't quite understand

173
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:48,600
why you stay here.

174
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,380
There is a saying here:

175
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:52,440
'Find a Hubei teacher for studies,

176
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,840
and a Hubei doctor for medical treatment.'

177
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:56,680
Aiding Xinjiang is not easy.

178
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,720
Mr. Yin and his team came all the way here,

179
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,120
taking the hardest path.

180
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,760
I am a local,

181
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,280
so I should stay.

182
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:07,080
Okay.

183
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,680
Have a safe trip.

184
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,490
What do you think

185
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,360
if I stay?
